The most depressing aspect of the "Are games art?", the assumption, from both sides, that were games to be art, they would be more valuable.
A game designer is respected for their ability to control.  The invisible puppet, that rewards the player for their unknowing obedience.
To play, is to reject optimisation, and should be more respected than the design, description and investigation of games.  Play is activism.
Many game designers, journalists & researchers distance themselves from mere players by emphasising the importance of their work.
Any task taken that is perceived not to be productive brings shame.  Hence games have a lower rung on society's ladder of mediums.
